    <instructions>1. Cut sweet onion into sections, then dice in food processor
2. Saute onion in olive oil in large pan until glazed
3. Add Italian Sausage to pan and cook until done
4. Add tomato paste and spaghetti sauce to pan
5. Simmer until flavors are mixed
6. Grate the mozzarella cheese withe a box grater
7. Put a small amount of spaghetti sauce in the bottom of a 9” x 13” pyrex pan
8. Layer the lasagna into the pyrex pan in three layers in the following order: noodles, spaghetti sauce, ricotta, parmesan and mozzarella
9. Bake in a 350-degree oven for ?? minutes</instructions>
